<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="513" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[763,1356,289,716]" pageId="29" pageNumber="513">
Seven subspecies have been previously recognized, but three (campestris, elongata, and 
<taxonomicName box="[830,900,486,519]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Vampyrodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="513" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">major</taxonomicName>
) are considered synonymous of nominate subspecies based on morphometric and molecular data. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
